Author-Name:    Evans, David S
Title:   Tests of Alternative Theories of Firm Growth. 
Journal: Journal of Political Economy
Pages: 657-74
Issue: 4
Volume: 95
Year: 1987
Month:  August 
Abstract:
  This study examines the relationships among firm growth, firm size, and
 firm age for a sample of manufacturing firms between 1976 and 1982. Firm
 growth is found to decrease with firm age and firm size. These findings
 are robust to alternative assumptions concerning the effects of sample
 censoring and the functional form of the growth relationship. The inverse
 growth-age relationship is consistent with a theory of firm learning
 proposed by Boyan Jovanovic while the inverse growth-size relationship is
 inconsistent with a number of theories that assume or imply Gibrat's law.  Copyright 1987 by University of Chicago Press.
