Author-Name:    Judd, Kenneth L
Title:   The Welfare Cost of Factor Taxation in a Perfect-Foresight Model. 
Journal: Journal of Political Economy
Pages: 675-709
Issue: 4
Volume: 95
Year: 1987
Month:  August 
Abstract:
  This paper examines the marginal efficiency cost of various factor taxes
 in a dynamic general-equilibrium model. The au thor solves for the excess
 burden of anticipated and unanticipated, t emporary and permanent, tax
 policies. Using a range of estimates for taste and technology parameters,
 he finds excess burdens larger than those indicated by previous studies
 that use static models. These exc ess burdens are sensitive to parameter
 values and timing. However, th e rankings of alternative tax policies turn
 out to be insensitive to structural parameter values.  Copyright 1987 by University of Chicago Press.
