Author-Name:    Rogerson, William P
Title:   The Dissipation of Profits by Brand Name Investment and Entry when Price Guarantees Quality. 
Journal: Journal of Political Economy
Pages: 797-809
Issue: 4
Volume: 95
Year: 1987
Month:  August 
Abstract:
  Two previous models of the dissipation of profits generated by the use of
 quality-guaranteeing prices assumed that pro fits were dissipated through
 investment in brand-name capital and ent ry. The model of this paper
 allows both possibilities. It is shown th at both types of dissipation
 will, in general, occur and that brand-n ame investment will dissipate a
 greater share of profits as the elast icity of consumer response to
 brand-name investment grows larger.  Copyright 1987 by University of Chicago Press.
