Title:   An Equilibrium Model of Sectoral Reallocation. 
Journal: Journal of Political Economy
Pages: 824-34
Issue: 4
Volume: 95
Year: 1987
Month:  August 
Abstract:
  This paper constructs a two-period, two-sector model in which there are
 permanent sectoral shocks. It analyzes the equilibrium path of individual
 labor supply, sectoral em ployment, and duration of unemployment in
 response to these shocks. E quilibrium allocations are shown to be easy to
 characterize and compa rative statistics results are provided.  Copyright 1987 by University of Chicago Press.
